The paper discusses a magnetic skyrmion-based artificial synapse device for neuromorphic systems, which involves the use of micromagnetic simulations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the study of magnetic properties and their manipulation, which falls under cs.EM (Electromagnetism). Additionally, the paper discusses micromagnetic simulations, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed device also involves the use of electronic circuits, which can be categorized under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of skyrmionic devices, which can be categorized under cs.ES (Embedded Systems).
